==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forereach
<hw>Fore*reach"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>To advance or gain upon; -- said of a vessel that gains upon
another when sailing closehauled.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forereach</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Forereach
<hw>Fore*reach"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>To shoot
ahead, especially when going in stays.</def> <rj><au>R. H. Dana,
Jr.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foreread</ent>⟦br⟧
